    [
      {
        "text": "Perhaps the most interesting feature in the history of"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Southern California islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is the story of the \""
      },
      {
        "text": "Lost Woman of San Nicholas Island",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" who was deserted and recovered years ago."
      },
      {
        "text": "Her cave",
        "entity_key": "re_lwcave",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and place of residence has never been found. During the coming week an attempt is to be made to find it, but the principal object of the expedition is to survey the big Indian mound on"
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". It represents the accumulations of centuries."
      },
      {
        "text": "Commodore Burnham",
        "entity_key": "burnham",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of the yacht"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Diego",
        "entity_key": "sh_sandiego",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "is to make the trip, and he will have as his guests"
      },
      {
